3. Argentina

Fraud and a few glasses of fine wine goes together for many men in Argentina.

While the habit of lying is widespread in Latin American countries, a study in 2014 highlighted the high level of deception – according to the Survey of Personality and Attachment, 44% of Argentina’s men are dishonest during courtship.

Perhaps they are inspired by Alberto Olmedo, the wildly famous comedian who cheated on his wife three times while she was dying. Another main reason for deception seems to be that men simply don’t want to come across as “too needy.”

Overall, it seems that the Argentinians want to create the illusion of perfection, whether it is a perfect relationship, marriage or an ability to raise a perfect family.

4. Germany

A study conducted by the University of Ulm in Germany revealed that women in the country think men are the least trustworthy during courtship.

While almost 10% of Germans believe that first dates should regard only business dinner conversations and not include any discussion of personal matters, 17% of the respondents claim they would lie to their partners.

They say lies are acceptable to make the potential spouse and relatives feel better.
